strnlght@netcom.com (David Sternlight) writes:

>>Quoting from the FCC's part 97.311 (rules for amateur radio):
>>
>>(c) Only the following types of SS emission transmissions are
>>authorized (hybrid SS emissions transmissions involving both
>>spreading techniques are prohibited):
[ SS rules omitted]

>I guess that means that with the right equipment, neither approach is
>secure against rich, smart eavesdroppers, though they will thwart Joe
>Curious and his Radio Shack scanner.

These rules are applicable only to amateur radio. Other amateur regs
specify rules on maintaining code sequences in your logbook so the
FCC can decode your SS stuff, allowable LFSR feedback combos, etc.
I'm sure that once you leave the amateur service, all sorts of
wonderful possibilities open up... subject, of course, to available
bandwidth.
-Steve
